GulfTalent.com
Customer Order Service Team Leader
AkzoNobel
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 5 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
The jobholder will operate out of AkzoNobel ME headquarters in Dubai, UAE and will manage a team of customer order service representatives based in the UAE. This position will be responsible for ensuring a high standard of service delivery to all AkzoNobel customers and will be expected to initiate and implement proactive, as well as corrective, actions as needed in order to ensure that an excellent standard of service and a high level of customer satisfaction are maintained.
Role and Responsibilities:
• Responsible for
the development and maintenance of standards, policies and procedures regarding customer service
• Give guidance and counseling to team members to create an engaged, motivated and technically capable team working to their potential
• Serve as communication link between external customers and internal stakeholders
• Ensure In Time & In Full dispatch of deliveries to customers and reliable flow of information between COS and all internal/external stakeholders
• Responsible for ensuring timely invoicing in system and correct and timely processing of credit notes as per ME Authority Matrix
• Investigate customer complaints in cooperation with other departments and respond as appropriate
• Respond to customer inquiries/communications as required.
• Review the Outstanding Order Report daily for pre-emptive action planning with internal stakeholders to ensure customer satisfaction
• Identify any process gaps and/or opportunities for improvement in the Planning-COS-Warehouse-Logistics process interaction
REQUIREMENTS
Profile:
The ideal candidate will have a Bachelor’s Degree and a minimum of 5 years progressive customer service or direct marketing experience with added exposure to supervisory activities. You will have a hands-on approach to management with a willingness to get involved in day-to-day processing and attention to detail. You demonstrate excellent people management and leadership skills and you work well under pressure. You will have excellent problem solving skills and you will be able to juggle many projects and issues at one time.
The ideal candidate will have excellent MS Office skills – specifically Excel/Word/Outlook. You will also have a good working knowledge of MFG Pro.
ABOUT THE COMPANY
AkzoNobel is a leading global paints and coatings company and a major producer of specialty chemicals. We supply industries and consumers worldwide with innovative products and are passionate about developing sustainable answers for our customers. Our portfolio includes well-known brands such as Dulux, Sikkens, International and Eka. Headquartered in Amsterdam, the Netherlands, we are consistently ranked as one of the leaders in the area of sustainability. With operations in more than 80 countries, our 50,000 people around the world are committed to excellence and delivering Tomorrow’s Answers Today™.
